      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'An obese 26-year-old man has an 8-hour history of severe dysuria, stranguria,
    and suprapubic and perineal pain with fever. On examination, he has suprapubic
    tenderness, and his prostate is enlarged, boggy, and exquisitely tender. Urinalysis
    shows pyuria. He continues to complain of symptoms despite insertion of a Foley
    catheter and has persistent fever following 30 hours of intravenous gentamicin
    and ampicillin. Culture grew Escherichia coli.

    

    What is the best
    next step?'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
